Astute – very clever and quick to understand
Example: She made an astute decision in business.
Bizarre – very strange or unusual
Example: That was a bizarre dream.
Candid – honest and direct
Example: He gave a candid opinion.
Deliberate – done on purpose
Example: It was a deliberate mistake.
Euphoria – a feeling of great happiness
Example: She felt euphoria after hearing the news.
Futile – having no result or useless
Example: Their efforts were futile.
Genuine – real or true
Example: This is a genuine product.
Hinder – to create difficulties
Example: Noise can hinder concentration.
Impeccable – perfect, without mistakes
Example: Her performance was impeccable.
Keen – very eager or interested
Example: He is keen to learn new skills.
